						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Koṅgu, Vikrama Chōḻa, Year 3+1 = 1259 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers a letter from the officer Akaḷaṅka-nāḍāḻvān to the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> and <hi rend="italic">ūrāḷikaḷ</hi> of Tiṅgaḷūr, asking them to conduct the Paṅguni festival in the temple of Chandrapurīśvaram-uḍaiyār using some tax on oil <hi rend="italic">(iṟaiyeṇṇai)</hi> and some paddy income from the village.</p>						

